The paper deals with fairness in cooperative games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of Renyi entropy and the connection to welfare economics suggests information theory (cs.IT) as another possible sub-category. The algorithms and computational complexity analysis involve data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of worst-case analysis and optimization techniques suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a possible sub-category as well.
